			<common:synonyms xml:lang="en">調味料;香辛料,香料</common:synonyms>
			<classificationInformation>
				<common:classification>
					<common:category level="0">Materials production</common:category>
					<common:category level="1">Food and renewable raw materials</common:category>
				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">香料 is a general term for things that emit odours. It is a chemical substance that can emit fragrance or provide flavor. They have a pleasant aroma and will volatilize at room temperature. Spices have played an important role in human history. In ancient times, due to the underdeveloped food preservation technology, people needed to pickle food to preserve the autumn harvest. Spices were needed as raw materials for pickling food. The demand for spices and food additives has increased, whether in variety or quantity. In Chinese history, Zhang Qian of the Han Dynasty opened a commercial road to the Western Regions, bringing back sesame and pepper as one of the important commodities.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">香料是散发气味的东西的总称。它是一种能散发香味或提供味道的化学物质。它们具有宜人的香气，并会在室温下挥发。香料在人类历史上扮演着重要角色。在古代，由于食物保存技术不发达，人们需要腌制食物来保存秋天的收获。腌制食物需要香料作为原料。人们对香料和食品添加剂的需求，无论在种类还是数量上，都与日俱增。在中国历史上，汉朝的张骞开辟了通往西域的商路，带回的重要商品之一就是芝麻和胡椒。</common:generalComment>
